An amber-red colored ale with an aroma that combines English hops and fruity esters.  A light malt flavor that fades to a clean, crisp hop finish.

Reddish amber colored beer. Nice balance between the sweetness of caramel malt and on the other hand fresh hop bitterness.
Genuine quality - Rich Taste
A clean, crisp lager brewed in the classic tradition only the finest hops, spring barley and pure Jamaican water.

These types of beer production using wheat ale malt, accompanied by a classic pale barley malt. Ultrafine and light taste of this beer gives the aromatic varieties of hops. Beer is unfiltered. Ideal for thirst quenching.

High quality golden beer with a balanced taste of maltiness aroma and rich toasty flavors obtained during long brewing. Produced from high-quality barley grown in the T?rvete region.

Brewed from the finest wheat germ, the full flavour of Macau Beer reflects the true spirit of Macanese culture. Enjoy the only beer brewed in Macau.

High quality beer with golden yellow colour, with pleasant bitterness and pure taste produced of 11% beer malt with a content of 4, 5 % vol. alcohol. 

Produced from the basic raw materials: Water, malt, hops, and beer yeast.

Skopsko Mlado pivo is unfiltered beer and still has visible traces of yeast. The taste of Mlado Pivo is slightly specific appreciated by beer lover! Mlado Pivo is a fresh beer and stays perfect for only a few days. Therefore we set up a unique way of distribution to guarantee the freshness at all times. It is only available as Draught Beer and you will find it in limited number of locations throughout Skopje.

Anchor Smooth pilsener beer has been enjoyed for its crisp, smooth and refreshing taste since 1933. Today Anchor is still brewed in the pilsen tradition but with special aromatic European hops to give you an even richer, smoother taste.

A crisp champagne-like beer with fine bubbles and a fruity, spicy aroma. The crisp clean malt character and delicate fruit notes in this beer are complemented by a slight citrus flavor from dry hopping with Bavarian Noble hops. Bottle conditioning adds another layer of complexity and light spice notes.

Colour and sight: light golden, compact and fine foam, good lacing.
Scent: nice, clear lager smell, a bit sulphury, good hop aromas
Flavour: Light malt sweet, pleasant bitterness, balanced and rich flavour. Slightly sweet and bitter aftertaste towards the end.

Deep stone-red colour, cloudy because of the used wheat beer. A compact head. 

Strong presence of the strawberry bouquet. 
Flavour: Very mild, sweet fruity beer, with an excellent balance between sweet and sour (a result of the fruit used). This makes the beer very enjoyable to drink.

Deep wine red, cloudy because of the wheat beer. Very fine, compact and lacing pink foam. 

The wonderful raspberry aroma perfectly counterbalances the wheat beer with its coriander and orange zest notes. 

Sweet raspberry mouthfeel with the expected longlasting raspberry effect in the aftertaste. This is a very enjoyable raspberry beer with an excellent sweet-sour balance.

Golden yellow, cloudy because of the wheat beer. A very persistent lacing head. 

You discover aromas of mango, apricot, peach and a subtle passion. 

Savouring this beer is quite complex, because of the use of various fruits. The predominant taste is peach and apricot.

Deep red colour, slightly cloudy because of the used wheat beer. Very compact and pink lace and head. 
Scent: The flavour of wild sour cherries and cherry stones. 

Soft and sweet fruity beer with a touch of nuts (cherry stones) and a sourish aftertaste, coming from the sour cherries. Excellent balance between the wheat beer and the wild sour cherries.
Very mild, sweet fruity beer, with an excellent balance between sweet and sour (a result of the fruit used). This makes the beer very enjoyable to drink.

Behold the stunning crimson hues through the inky blackness. Inhale the noble Hallertau hops, spicy and floral. Savor the flavors redolent of English toffee, rich mocha, sweet molasses, candied currants and a hint of anise. We highly recommend cellaring additional bottles, as the Czar will continue to mature and become denser and more complex with age.

Known as "The King of Beers," Budweiser was first introduced by Adolphus Busch in 1876 and it's still brewed with the same high standards today. Budweiser is a medium-bodied, flavorful, crisp American-style lager. Brewed with the best barley malt and a blend of premium hop varieties, it is an icon of core American values like optimism and celebration.

Maharaja is derived from the sanskrit words mahat, - "great" and rajan - "king". Much like its namesake, this imperial IPA is regal, intense and mighty. With hops and malts as his servants, he rules both with a heavy hand. The Maharaja flaunts his authority over a deranged amount of hops: tangy, vibrant and pungent along with an insane amount of malted barley - fashioning a dark amber hue and exquisite malt essence. This newest Avery Dictator completes the "Dictator Series" joining the likes of The Kaiser & The Czar. Be aware that The Maharaja is a limited release only available for the summer. Welcome to his kingdom! 
Editor?s Note: the 2007 version was 9.78%.
2014 - 10.2%

Ini jenis bir 'zero' alkohol. Bir Pletok termasuk langka. Mereka yang bisa membuat minuman ini kian  sedikit jumlahnya. Dari dua belas macam rempah, itu menurut Ariani, antara lain jahe merah, kayu secang, kayu manis, kapulaga dan gula pasir. Semua bahan direbus menjadi satu. Setiap satu kilogram bahan rempah, dicampur dengan lima liter air. Lalu disaring hingga dua kali. Tujuannya memisahkan rempah dari airnya. sumber :http://wap.vivanews.com/news/read/161207-bir-pletok-betawi-yang-langka

Samaels is a super-caramelly, oak-aged English-style strong ale. Perhaps the least hoppy (sacrilege here at Avery!) beer we?ve brewed, to accentuate the malt. The oak is very apparent in this rich and high gravity ale, adding additional depth and complexity with a woody and cask-like nose and a pronounced vanilla flavor on the palate. With the addition of a more roasted malt in 2007, Samaels now delivers subtle bitterness to add balance to the natural sweetness. Cellarable for 10+ years.

beer_description: The Kaiser once said, ?Give me a woman who loves beer and I will conquer the world.? If the Kaiser and his significant other had tipped this bottle, we?d all be ?sprechenden Deutsch!? We took all that is good in a traditional Oktoberfest ? gorgeous, deep copper sheen, massive malty backbone and spicy, floral, pungent noble hops ? then intensified each into this, an Imperial Oktoberfest.

Bintang Beer is a lager type of beer. The distinctive taste of Bintang comes from its quality ingredients and meticulous brewing process. Famed for its modest ester aroma, mild hoppy flavor and bitterness as well as a crisp and refreshing aftertaste, this 4.7%-alcohol beer has been serving as a local favorite for over 80 years. Bintang is brewed from selected malt, hops and water and processed with high quality standard.

The Reverend, was created in tribute to the life of our friend Tom Boogaard?s grandfather, an ordained Episcopal Reverend. Tom was inspired by the life of his grandfather and wanted to create a tribute beer that contained his sterling traits. True to the spirit and character of the departed Reverend, this beer is strong willed, assertive, and pure of heart.

Bridge Road Brewers have created their own take on a more traditional beer style ? India Pale Ale, originally a heavily hopped beer developed for the long haul from England to India by boat.

Fresh hops were added to the barrel and the alcohol was bolstered to ensure the beer went the distance on the high seas. Bling, is a huge beer, with all the bells and whistles. This ale is armed to the teeth with hops and studded with 24 carrot modified malts. At Bridge Road we've gone all out to make an IPA that screams hops and malt but still keeps balance in mind. Try matching this beer it with anything spicy or enjoy this malt and hop mouth full on its own. We love it, and hope you can too.

A crisp, refreshing, light-bodied malt-flavored beer with a well-balanced finish. A Lager that drinks like a Pilsner. A liquid embodiment of living life to the fullest. A beverage made from pure spring water and the choicest hops. A beer with such good taste, it?s chosen you to drink it.
brewery.brewery_name: Cervecer?a Cuauht?moc Moctezuma S.A. de C.V.

beer_description: Boulevard Unfiltered Wheat Beer is a lively, refreshing ale with a natural citrusy flavor and distinctive cloudy appearance. This easy drinking American-style wheat beer has become our most popular offering, and the best-selling craft beer in the Midwest.

For this inaugural installment of collaboration brews, we invited distinguished Belgian brewer Jean-Marie Rock to join our own Steven Pauwels for a zymological alliance. A starkly simple recipe combined with a painstakingly complex brewing process produce an Imperial Pilsner of subtle elegance and delicately balanced contrasts. First wort hopping, a very old technique in which hops normally added late in the boil are put in at the beginning, and allowed to steep for a much longer time, gives the beer an especially refined hop aroma and flavor. The 100% Pilsner malt makes a clear, yet restrained statement, answered by a stead, harmonious chorus of Saaz hop bitterness, echoes of which linger in the dry, crisp finish.

brewery.brewery_name: Cervecer?a Cuauht?moc Moctezuma S.A. de C.V.

beer_description: Otro buen acierto de las cervecerias independientes. Buen cuerpo y un sabor a lupulo muy acentado al final, que le da ese sabor peculiar, encontrado en cervezas de la zona de Republica checa y el sur este de alemania.

Like India Pale Ale, the classic Imperial Stouts were originally brewed with high levels of alcohol and hops to withstand the rigors of a long sea journey, not to India but to Imperial Russia and the Baltic States. Our version is an over-the-top riff on the style, with a huge grain bill featuring several kinds of malted barley, wheat, rye, oats, and spelt. Robust grain and coffee flavors are counterbalanced by date and plum notes from the Belgian yeast. To add extra complexity and depth, this Imperial Stout is made up of a blend of freshly brewed beer and several barrel-aged beers, carefully balanced. Za Vas!

Victoria , a pilsener-vienna type beer, is the most traditional out of Modelo?s brand portfolio. Unique for its bitterness and strong flavor which instantly pleases even the most demanding consumer. With more than 135 years of excellence, Victoria is one of the oldest beers produced in Mexico.

Charlie Papazian and Fred Eckhart are the men who launched a thousand breweries. Their writing on the art of homebrewing and steadfast promotion of beer culture helped propel the craft brewing movement. Charlie and Fred agreed to work with us on this special ale in honor of our 30th anniversary. This Imperial Helles Bock is a testament to the ever-evolving brewer?s art. Bold yet balanced with distinct toasted malt character, moderate sweetness and clean and floral hops.
beer_name: 30th Anniversary - Charlie, Fred & Ken's Imperial Helles Bock

beer_description:
Our take on the West Coast-style Double India Pale Ale, The Oracle places hop intensity first and foremost, making only the slightest concession to malt and balance.

The fireworks start with the aromatic punch of dry-hop sessions with hop varieties from the Pacific Northwest. Resinous, citrusy hop flavors mixed with aggressive bitterness from a massive kettle addition deliver on that aromatic promise.
Truly, this brew is undefinable. But double black ipa is as close as we can get.

Flaked oats provide a smoothing effect on the sharper roasted characteristics of typical stout specialty malts. Oats add a mild nutty, breakfast cereal flavor to the chocolate & coffee notes of the roasted malts. Hop character is secondary: bitterness is present for balance, while aroma is only a background layer.

beer_description:
Pours a pale gold with low carbonation and a thin head which soon dissipates. Appearance is a little underwhelming, due to the carbonation problem.

Aromas of malted milk, barley fields, and not a lot in the way of hops. No adjuncts, this beer smells organic like it claims, but isn't very interesting.
New Zealand hop included

Taste is like a slightly worse watered down version of the aroma. light alcohol. slightly more offensive sweaty socks character. less vegetal and less resembling a bad champagne (both of which would have been preferred). touch of bitterness. clingy unpleasant aftertast.

Brewed by: 
Asahi Breweries Ltd
Review:
Everyone else is right, and I was very surprised to find that it was a full-strength beer of 5% ABV. It is totally inoffensive, which really offends me.
The good thing is that is was only 200yen ($2+) in the vending machine compared with Asahi Dry which was 270yen ($2.70+). However, I think the "karakuchi" of Asahi Dry is worth the extra $0.70.
My beer wouldn't skimp on me, so why should I skimp on my beer?
Double fermentation kvass made of true ingredients

This titanic, immensely viscous stout is loaded with inimitable flavors of chocolate-covered caramel and coffee and hide a hefty 65 IBUs underneath the smooth blanket of malt. It is made with enormous amounts of two-row malt, chocolate malt, roasted barley, flaked oats and hops.
